text: Nymphon leptocheles is a species of sea spider first described by Georg Ossian Sars in 1888. The species greatly resembles other members of the genus Nymphon, and species identification from morphological traits alone is therefore a complex task.Nymphon leptocheles at Marine Species Identification Portal ==Habitat== The species inhabits the sublittoral zone and occurs amongst hydroids and sea anemones. ==Diet== N. leptocheles feeds on coelenterates. ==References== Category:Pycnogonids Category:Taxa named by Georg Ossian Sars Category:Animals described in 1888
title: Nymphon leptocheles
